<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHINING AND WINNING: DOES IT REALLY MATTER? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So poor Bret Johnson decided to quit UCLA because he wouldn't be starting? 
Isn't that a shame. 
</P>
<P>
In high school, when Johnson was El Toro's sophomore quarterback, I was the 
starting center. One thing I'll always remember is that when the going got 
tough, Bret whined, sniveled and pointed fingers -- at everybody except 
himself. 
</P>
<P>
Bret never lost a game because the other guy was better. Bret always lost 
because his teammates didn't block, the referee made a poor call or there was 
bad weather. In Bret Johnson's mind, Bret Johnson could do no wrong. I think 
UCLA fans will join me in saying good riddance. 
</P>
<P>
J. THOMPSON 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
</TEXT>
