<HEADLINE>
<P>
USC ALREADY DESERVES THE HEISMAN FOR HYPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Again this year, the USC publicity department has done a Hollywood job in 
preparation for the football season. They concentrated on their quarterback, 
Todd Marinovich, elevating him from a good sophomore quarterback to the point 
of being a Heisman Trophy candidate. 
</P>
<P>
It's too bad equally or more qualified Pac-10 quarterbacks such as Brad Gossen 
of Washington State, Bill Musgrave of Oregon and Paul Justin of Arizona State 
don't attend schools with the same promotional skills. 
</P>
<P>
ROGER GLAZBROOK 
</P>
<P>
Glendora 
