<LENGTH>
<P>
69 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The fifth annual Greater Los Angeles Criterium, conducted by the L.A. County 
Dept. of Parks and Recreation, will be held on the streets of Monterey Park and 
East Los Angeles on Sunday, with the first race scheduled for 7 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Eight of the races are open to riders licensed by the U.S. Bicycling 
Federation. Two others are open to the public, with the men competing at 11:45 
a.m. and the women at 12:45 p.m. 
</P>
