<HEADLINE>
<P>
COULD HUSSEIN GET HIS TEETH INTO SETTLEMENT? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW DELHI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The crisis in the Persian Gulf could be settled peacefully if Iraqi President 
Saddam Hussein got his teeth fixed, the personal dentist to the late guru Osho 
Rajneesh said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Swami Devageet said that Rajneesh, a mystic who was expelled from the United 
States in 1985 and died in January, discovered a year ago that "man's animal 
past, including his aggressive instincts, are mysteriously stored in the human 
dental structure." 
</P>
<P>
In a telex from the commune that Rajneesh founded in Poona, Devageet said that 
Hussein could become "a blissful human being instead of a blistering warmonger" 
if he submitted to tooth-centered character analysis. 
</P>
<P>
"It may sound absurd, but it's a lot cheaper than a third World War," Devageet 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
