<HEADLINE>
<P>
UNICEF SEEKING $5.2 MILLION FOR REFUGEE AID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.N. Children's Fund, which last week appealed for $585,000 to aid 
thousands of refugees streaming into Jordan from Kuwait and Iraq, raised its 
target nearly tenfold Friday to $5.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
"The numbers of affected persons continue to increase daily as more cross the 
borders. Those crossing now are generally of more limited means and therefore 
in need of greater support," UNICEF Executive Director James Grant said in a 
press statement. 
</P>
<P>
UNICEF said half a million people had entered Jordan since Iraq's invasion of 
Kuwait on Aug. 2. It said as many as half a million additional evacuees, poorer 
and more desperate, are expected to arrive soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
