<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: EL RIO; 
</P>
<P>
BOY, 15, ACCIDENTALLY SHOT BY A FRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 15-year-old El Rio boy underwent emergency surgery Friday after being 
accidentally shot by a friend who was examining a handgun, a Ventura County 
sheriff's spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Adane suffered arm and chest wounds in the 11:15 a.m. shooting on Balboa 
Street, Senior Sheriff's Deputy Steve Joneson said. 
</P>
<P>
Adane was listed in fair condition after surgery at St. John's Regional Medical 
Center, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
According to the Sheriff's Department, Raymond Coronel, 15, was holding a 
.22-caliber pistol as he and Adane examined the weapon. The gun discharged, and 
a bullet struck Adane in the arm and entered his chest. 
</P>
<P>
Joneson said that investigators have deemed the shooting an accident and that 
no charges have been filed. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
