<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 16; Column 2 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
106 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADAM BENSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Muir 38, Palmdale 13 -- Senior quarterback Sedrick Thomas completed 12 of 16 
passes for 223 yards as Muir overcame a 13-0 deficit at Pasadena City College. 
</P>
<P>
The Mustangs tied the score shortly before halftime and took the lead midway 
through the third quarter when defensive tackle Aaron Shakoor tackled Palmdale 
quarterback Rodney Williams in the end zone for a safety. 
</P>
<P>
A 20-point fourth quarter, highlighted by two touchdowns by Thomas, put the 
game away. 
</P>
<P>
Muir fell behind 7-0 on the first play of scrimmage when Williams pitched to 
tailback Anthony Ortega, who lofted a 79-yard touchdown pass to Brian Porter. 
ADAM BENSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
