<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION BRIEFS: B'NAI B'RITH DECIDES TO LET WOMEN JOIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A convention of B'nai B'rith International in Dallas recently amended the 
group's constitution to allow women to be admitted as members of the Jewish 
service organization. 
</P>
<P>
A women's affiliate, B'nai B'rith Women, had threatened to break away from the 
central organization unless B'nai B'rith dropped its restriction limiting 
membership to men. 
</P>
<P>
Seymour D. Reich, president of B'nai B'rith, said women may now be full and 
equal partners with men in the organization and are eligible for offices at all 
levels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
