<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS' LATE SURGE OVERCOMES MARINA, 7-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WESTMINSTER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The legend has gone, but the understudy is filling in admirably. 
</P>
<P>
Todd Gragnano, who quarterbacked Los Alamitos High School to three straight 
Empire League championships, is now at the University of Nebraska. 
</P>
<P>
But senior quarterback John Collins learned enough in three years to hit Tyler 
Cashman with a 29-yard touchdown pass in the fourth quarter, giving Los 
Alamitos a 7-3 victory over host Marina High. 
</P>
<P>
"Todd's a good friend of mine," Collins said, "so I've been around him, and 
when I get out there, I think, 'I gotta do what he did.' Although I know my 
limitations, I have high expectations." 
</P>
<P>
Collins completed 14 of 23 passes for 158 yards. 
</P>
<P>
With Marina leading, 3-0, in the fourth quarter, Collins lofted a wobbly pass 
to Cashman for the only touchdown of the game, and Eric Wallace kicked the 
extra point. 
</P>
<P>
Marina's No. 1 fullback, Shawn Fulford, carried the ball more times for more 
yards -- 26 for 113 -- than the entire Los Alamitos team (13 for 65). 
</P>
<P>
Fulford's two-yard apparent touchdown in the first quarter was nullified by a 
penalty, and Dan Armstrong gave Marina the early lead with a 28-yard field 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
Los Alamitos Coach John Barnes was not satisfied. HEATHER SMALLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
