<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANA HILLS OVERPOWERS FOUNTAIN VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DANA POINT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a sluggish first quarter, Dana Hills High School dominated Fountain 
Valley en route to a 27-6 victory Friday night at Spencer Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The Dolphins got two rushing touchdowns in both the second and fourth quarters, 
and outgained the Barons in total offense, 267-75, in the final three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Fountain Valley scored on the game's first possession on quarterback Marcos 
Diaz's four-yard touchdown pass to David Dardis. From that point, however, Dana 
Hills controlled the game. 
</P>
<P>
Marcus Jenkins put the Dolphins on the board with a 26-yard touchdown run with 
3:52 left to play in the first half, and John Ashley's extra point gave Dana 
Hills the lead for good. 
</P>
<P>
Dana Hills' Shaun Coleman scored the first of his two touchdowns on a one-yard 
run with four seconds to go in the second quarter. The touchdown was set up by 
Marcelle Franklin's 30-yard gain on a screen pass from Albie Sukut with 16 
seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman scored again from a yard out early in the fourth quarter to give Dana 
Hills a 20-6 lead. Scott Duster completed the scoring with a 47-yard end run 
with 3:46 left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
After the first quarter, Diaz was 3 for 15 and finished 7 for 20 for 95 yards 
and the touchdown. Franklin led Dana Hills with 58 yards on 13 carries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
