<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
AGENCY URGES PUBLIC TO ATTEND MEETING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Citizens interested in learning about the proposed Foothill Transportation 
Corridor that could run through the city can attend a public meeting Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The Transportation Corridor Agencies meeting will be held at 7 p.m. in the 
Community Center, 100 N. Calle Seville. 
</P>
<P>
"This meeting is an opportunity for residents to learn more about the 
corridor's proposed alignments through San Clemente," said Councilwoman Holly 
Veale, who is the council's representative on the Transportation Corridor 
Agencies. "This meeting is an opportunity for the citizens of San Clemente to 
be part of the planning process." 
</P>
<P>
By voicing opinions, the public can help the agency "reach an informed 
decision," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Further information can be obtained by contacting Laura Coley Eisenberg, 
associate environmental analyst for the Transportation Corridor Agencies, at 
(714) 557-3298, Ext. 326. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
